{"id":11606,"title":"3D Nanofibrillar Cellulose hydrogel platform for long-term human islet culture","title_html":"3D Nanofibrillar Cellulose hydrogel platform for long-term human islet culture","image":{"source":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/default_protocol.png","placeholder":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/default_protocol.png"},"doi":"dx.doi.org\/10.17504\/protocols.io.pjwdkpe","doi_status":2,"uri":"3d-nanofibrillar-cellulose-hydrogel-platform-for-l-pjwdkpe","type_id":1,"published_on":1572895333,"parent_protocols":[],"parent_collections":[],"version_id":0,"created_on":1524092939,"categories":null,"creator":{"name":"Yi-Ju Chen","affiliation":"University of Pennsylvania","affiliations":[{"affiliation":"University of Pennsylvania","url":"","is_default":1}],"username":"yiju-chen","link":null,"image":{"source":"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/pr-journal\/x4mjfww.jpg","placeholder":"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/pr-journal\/x4mjfww.jpg"},"badges":[{"id":2,"image":{"source":"\/img\/badges\/bronze.svg","placeholder":"\/img\/badges\/bronze.svg"},"name":"Author"}],"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false},"journal":null,"journal_name":null,"journal_link":null,"article_citation":null,"public":1,"has_versions":0,"link":null,"total_collections":0,"number_of_steps":5,"authors":[{"name":"Yi-Ju Chen","affiliation":"University of Pennsylvania","affiliations":[],"username":"yiju-chen","link":null,"image":{"source":"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/pr-journal\/x4mjfww.jpg","placeholder":"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/pr-journal\/x4mjfww.jpg"},"badges":[],"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false},{"name":"Ben Z. Stanger","affiliation":"University of Pennsylvania","affiliations":[],"username":null,"link":null,"image":{"source":null,"placeholder":null},"badges":[],"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false}],"versions":[],"groups":[],"has_subprotocols":0,"is_subprotocol":0,"is_bookmarked":1,"can_be_copied":1,"can_remove_fork":1,"forks_count":{"private":0,"public":0},"access":{"can_view":1,"can_remove":0,"can_add":0,"can_edit":0,"can_publish":0,"can_get_doi":0,"can_share":1,"can_move":1,"can_move_outside":1,"can_transfer":1,"can_download":1,"is_locked":0},"guid":"8AC5BC12B9DA11E99CA40242AC110005","steps":[{"id":629885,"guid":"60E836FDEA57429C94A1B8291145421B","previous_id":630096,"previous_guid":"53F490AFC71D4A48B5678D0FBF419AA1","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"05EF484C2E7F424F9DE8C040F2081655","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Preparation of the nanofibrillar cellulose (NFC) hydrogel "}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"997B134A2A4C4033AE333AA229D6F2E7","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \":justify;\">Weigh the needed amount of NFC hydrogel (Growdex\u00ae) and mix it with CIT culture media at 1:1 ratio by vortexing to make a 0.75% (w\/v) hydrogel.<\/span><span style = \":justify;\"><\/span><\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"6843CD8DFCAD45ABA1785998503BA461","order_id":2,"type_id":26,"title":"notes","source":{"id":0,"parent_id":0,"uri":"","title":"","body":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">The NFC hydrogel (Growdex\u00ae) purchased from UPM Biochemicals is 1.5%. <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">For example, weigh 0.5g of NFC hydrogel (Growdex\u00ae) and mix it with 0.5 ml CIT media by vortexing. This could make 6 replicates of 0.75% hydrogel culture (80 ul for each replicate, see the Step 3). <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Low retention pipette tips should be used while handling the hydrogel. <\/div><\/div>","created_on":0,"changed_on":0,"creator":{"name":" ","affiliation":"","affiliations":[],"username":"","link":null,"image":{"source":"","placeholder":""},"badges":[],"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false},"comments":[]}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":629886,"guid":"8FB1D92A2483466CBDA511BBFE99CAF8","previous_id":629885,"previous_guid":"60E836FDEA57429C94A1B8291145421B","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"C030304AC720496FBE6307A19EBBFAAF","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Setup 3D human islet culture with NFC hydrogel"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"25E49F16A9614328ABAE2A6677CC1E32","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><ul style = \"list-style-type:disc;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Human islets are handpicked into Eppendorf tubes (50 islets per tube) and kept on the rack to allow the islets to settle by gravity. Remove excess media as much as possible.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Gently mixed 50 islets with 80 ul of 0.75% (w\/v) hydrogel and then dispensed it into an insert of Transwell. It should be avoided to generate air bubbles while mixing and dispensing the samples.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><span>Placed the NFC hydrogel culture into a humidified incubator (37 \u00baC, 5% CO<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">2<\/span><span>) for at least 15-30 min.<\/span><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><span>Carefully add 80 ul CIT media on top of the NFC hydrogel without disturbing it. Then, add 500 ul of CIT media at the plate well. This 3D NFC culture is maintained in\u00a0a humidified incubator at 37 \u00baC with 5% CO<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">2.<\/span><span><\/span><\/li><\/ul><\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"69DA2187198B4011B43AF1D8E08D0EAB","order_id":2,"type_id":26,"title":"notes","source":{"id":0,"parent_id":0,"uri":"","title":"","body":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">The low retention tips should be used for this step. <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">After overnight incubation, it should generate a thin layer of media on top of the NFC hydrogel.<\/div><\/div>","created_on":0,"changed_on":0,"creator":{"name":" ","affiliation":"","affiliations":[],"username":"","link":null,"image":{"source":"","placeholder":""},"badges":[],"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false},"comments":[]}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":629892,"guid":"C984089B6B0E4E0582214122225AB9C9","previous_id":629886,"previous_guid":"8FB1D92A2483466CBDA511BBFE99CAF8","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"E4711FE5D8B0435192E6FC0CEA1A3E1F","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Maintain long-term 3D islet NFC culture"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"AF257C5A38E545568E16EA2D2AAAA468","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \":justify;\">To maintain a\u00a03D NFC culture in a long-term, 100 ul of CIT media is added to the insert every 3 or 4 days. Replace media at the plat well (bottom) every two weeks.<\/span><span style = \":justify;\"><\/span><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":630096,"guid":"53F490AFC71D4A48B5678D0FBF419AA1","previous_id":null,"previous_guid":null,"modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"A17E3CCBB2EC49A2A88A91B23936EEF0","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Preparation of CIT culture media "}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"8735B8BF1FF34D339AB10ACA610D8FBF","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><ul style = \"list-style-type:disc;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Dissolve 10KU Heparin powder with 1 ml of CMRL1066, CIT modification base medium to\u00a0obtain Heparin solution (10 KU\/ml).<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Dissolve 100\u03bcg IGF-1 powder in 100\u03bcl of sterile 10 mM HCl solution to obtain IGF-1 solution (1 \u03bcg\/\u03bcl)<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Add 500 \u03bcl of Heparin solution (10 KU\/ml), 50\u00a0\u03bcl of IGF-1 solution (1 \u03bcg\/\u03bcl), and 10 ml of Human Serum Albumin Solution (25%) into 500 ml of CMRL1066, CIT modification base medium.\u00a0<\/li><\/ul><\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"ADF938EA77E14BDE852BA5A92781D027","order_id":2,"type_id":26,"title":"notes","source":{"id":0,"parent_id":0,"uri":"","title":"","body":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>The CIT culture media recipe used in this protocol is originally developed by the Clinical Islet Transplantation (CIT) Consortium and published at CellR4 2014; 2 (3):e981. <\/span><a href=\"http:\/\/www.cellr4.org\/article\/981\" style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\">http:\/\/www.cellr4.org\/article\/981<\/span><\/a><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">The composition of CIT media is CMRL1066, CIT Modification medium supplemented with 0.5% Human Albumin, 10 U\/ml Heparin, and 0.1 mg\/ml IGF-1.<\/div><\/div>","created_on":0,"changed_on":0,"creator":{"name":" ","affiliation":"","affiliations":[],"username":"","link":null,"image":{"source":"","placeholder":""},"badges":[],"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false},"comments":[]}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":630097,"guid":"0516E4BDFADC47A3A5F3987A25019A60","previous_id":629892,"previous_guid":"C984089B6B0E4E0582214122225AB9C9","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"1B3ADE3987754A6EB5D7A07A9FD274CA","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Retrieve islets from the NFC hydrogel"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"C628045544FE48C38031BA03E3A6F889","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><ul style = \"list-style-type:disc;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Remove the media from the plate well<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Mix\u00a050 ul GrowDase enzyme with 200 ul\u00a0CIT media and then add the mixture (250 ul in total) to an insert of the Transwell.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Add 300 ul of CIT media at the bottom (plate well).<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><span>Incubate overnight (12-16 hours) in\u00a0a humidified incubator at 37 \u00baC with 5% CO<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">2.\u00a0\u00a0<\/span><span><\/span><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Once hydrogel is digested, samples are ready\u00a0to be retrieved for further analysis.<\/li><\/ul><\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"A5095F4DEA524FABB1F23E43297D67B4","order_id":2,"type_id":26,"title":"notes","source":{"id":0,"parent_id":0,"uri":"","title":"","body":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">The NFC hydrogel can be digested within 8-12 hours by this setup.<\/div><\/div>","created_on":0,"changed_on":0,"creator":{"name":" ","affiliation":"","affiliations":[],"username":"","link":null,"image":{"source":"","placeholder":""},"badges":[],"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false},"comments":[]}},{"id":1054726,"guid":"AFD64EF164C84367B83323AAC506E432","order_id":3,"type_id":17,"title":"result","source":{"body":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">83 days cultured human islets retrieved from 3D NFC hydrogel platform<\/div><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/pr-journal\/x4hjfww.png\" \/><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0}],"document":null,"materials":[{"id":125959,"mol_weight":0,"name":"GrowDase enzyme","linfor":"","url":"http:\/\/www.upmbiochemicals.com\/Pages\/default.aspx","sku":"","cas_number":"","rrid":"","public":0,"vendor":{"name":"Contributed by users","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":null,"link":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io","image":{"source":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/1.png","placeholder":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/1.png"},"badges":[],"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false,"id":1},"can_edit":0,"stats":{"total_protocols":0}},{"id":125960,"mol_weight":0,"name":"GrowDex","linfor":"","url":"http:\/\/www.upmbiochemicals.com\/growdex\/Pages\/Default.aspx","sku":"","cas_number":"","rrid":"","public":0,"vendor":{"name":"Contributed by users","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":null,"link":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io","image":{"source":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/1.png","placeholder":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/1.png"},"badges":[],"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false,"id":1},"can_edit":0,"stats":{"total_protocols":0}},{"id":125961,"mol_weight":0,"name":"6.5 mm Transwell\u00ae with 8.0 \u00b5m Pore Polyester Membrane Insert, Sterile","linfor":"","url":"https:\/\/ecatalog.corning.com\/life-sciences\/b2c\/US\/en\/Permeable-Supports\/Inserts\/Transwell%C2%AE-Clear-Inserts%2C-Polyester-%28PET%29-membrane\/p\/3464?clear=true","sku":"3464","cas_number":"","rrid":"","public":0,"vendor":{"name":"Corning","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":null,"link":"https:\/\/www.corning.com\/worldwide\/en.html","image":{"source":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png","placeholder":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png"},"badges":[],"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false,"id":40},"can_edit":0,"stats":{"total_protocols":0}},{"id":125964,"mol_weight":0,"name":"CMRL 1066, CIT Modification, 500ml","linfor":"","url":"https:\/\/ecatalog.corning.com\/life-sciences\/b2c\/US\/en\/Media%2C-Sera%2C-and-Reagents\/Islet-Solutions\/Islet-Solutions-and-Reagents\/Corning%C2%AE-CMRL-1066%2C-Supplemented%2C-CIT-Modification\/p\/98-304-CV?lang=en","sku":" 98-304-CV","cas_number":"","rrid":"","public":0,"vendor":{"name":"Corning","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":null,"link":"https:\/\/www.corning.com\/worldwide\/en.html","image":{"source":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png","placeholder":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png"},"badges":[],"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false,"id":40},"can_edit":0,"stats":{"total_protocols":0}},{"id":125965,"mol_weight":0,"name":"Human Serum Albumin Solution\u201425%","linfor":"","url":"https:\/\/www.gembio.com\/product\/human-serum-albumin-solution-25","sku":"#800-120","cas_number":"","rrid":"","public":0,"vendor":{"name":"Contributed by users","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":null,"link":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io","image":{"source":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/1.png","placeholder":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/1.png"},"badges":[],"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false,"id":1},"can_edit":0,"stats":{"total_protocols":0}},{"id":125967,"mol_weight":0,"name":"Heparin sodium salt, 10KU","linfor":"","url":"https:\/\/www.sigmaaldrich.com\/catalog\/product\/sial\/h3149?lang=en&region=US","sku":"H3149-10KU","cas_number":"","rrid":"","public":0,"vendor":{"name":"Sigma Aldrich","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":null,"link":"http:\/\/sigmaaldrich.com","image":{"source":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png","placeholder":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png"},"badges":[],"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false,"id":17},"can_edit":0,"stats":{"total_protocols":0}},{"id":125968,"mol_weight":0,"name":"IGF-1 Recombinant Human Protein, 100\u03bcg","linfor":"","url":"https:\/\/www.fishersci.com\/shop\/products\/r-hu-igf-1\/phg0071","sku":"PHG0071","cas_number":"","rrid":"","public":0,"vendor":{"name":"Gibco - Thermo Fischer","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":null,"link":"https:\/\/www.thermofisher.com\/de\/de\/home\/brands\/gibco.html","image":{"source":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png","placeholder":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png"},"badges":[],"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false,"id":137},"can_edit":0,"stats":{"total_protocols":0}}],"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>It remains a challenge to maintain human islets\u00a0<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">ex vivo<\/span><span>\u00a0to provide a functional and sufficient source for clinical islet transplantation and an\u00a0<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">in vitro<\/span><span>\u00a0model for drug screening or basic biological studies. With a conventional culture method, islets lost their functionality and mass rapidly upon they were isolated from the native environment, which provides both mechanical and biological supports. By merging the advantage of transwell cultures and the mechanical properties provided by the wood-derived nanofibrillar cellulose (NFC) hydrogel, we developed a new islet\u00a0<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">ex vivo<\/span><span>\u00a0platform, which can preserve human islets up to 83 days with intact morphology similar to freshly isolated counterparts. Importantly, these long-term cultured human islets are still potent and can ameliorate hyperglycemia in diabetic mice post-transplantation. The platform is designed to be\u00a0user friendly\u00a0and easily adapted to help scientists overcome the difficulties in islet cultures. Furthermore, the application of this platform aims to provide a sufficient window for pre-transplantation islet assessment, a biobanking opportunity of human islets, and an\u00a0<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">in vitro<\/span><span>\u00a0model for human islet studies in drug-screening, stem cell-derived islet (beta)-like organoids maturation, and basic human islet biology.<\/span><\/div><\/div>","changed_on":1572895333}